### Where the Chatbot Traffic Actually Goes

With AI assistants increasingly standing in for search, it's worth a quick reality check on who's actually winning that traffic. Reuters Institute data shows 10% of global adults now use AI chatbots for news weekly (up from 7% a year ago), though only 4% click through to original sources — a real concern for publishers and marketers alike banking on referral traffic. Among the assistants themselves, ChatGPT still dominates web traffic share, with Gemini a distant second and Claude smaller globally but notably stronger in the U.S.

